entities.name: AI16Z
entities.description: A legacy token that is no longer the primary utility token of the elizaOS ecosystem. It remains tradable on decentralized exchanges but lacks utility within the current platform. The token has a deadline for migration to elizaOS.

entities.name: elizaOS
entities.description: An operating system or platform, focusing on cloud streaming and onchain capabilities. It functions as the successor to AI16Z, with elizaOS being the designated utility-forward token. The platform aims to provide EVM/onchain capabilities and ecosystem analytics.

entities.name: Twitter/X
entities.description: A social media platform for microblogging and real-time information sharing. It allows users to post and interact with short messages, images, and videos.

entities.name: Discord
entities.description: A voice-over-IP and instant messaging social platform designed for communities to interact on voice and text. It is organized into communities called 'servers', and each server can have multiple channels.

entities.name: EVM
entities.description: Ethereum Virtual Machine. A runtime environment for smart contracts on the Ethereum blockchain, enabling developers to deploy and execute decentralized applications. It is a core component of many blockchains.

entities.name: Spartan
entities.description: Unknown - needs research

entities.name: NPM
entities.description: A package manager for the JavaScript programming language, part of the Node.js ecosystem. It allows developers to discover, share, and use code packages.

entities.name: Hyperfy
entities.description: A platform that announced a v0.16.0 release with AI integrations and XR/VR improvements. It focuses on immersive experiences and has been developing AI capabilities.

entities.name: Starknet
entities.description: A decentralized scaling solution for Ethereum that allows dApps to achieve hyper-scale for compute, without sacrificing the benefits of Ethereum's security and decentralization. It operates as a Layer 2 network.

entities.name: GitHub
entities.description: A web-based platform for version control using Git. It provides a centralized repository for code, collaboration tools, and project management features for software development.

entities.name: Kraken
entities.description: A cryptocurrency exchange platform that provides a marketplace for buying, selling, and trading digital assets. It is one of the exchanges involved in the token swap process.

entities.name: Bithumb
entities.description: A South Korean cryptocurrency exchange platform. It is involved in the process of handling token swaps and has been a point of concern for the Korean community.

entities.name: Solana Network
entities.description: A blockchain platform designed for high performance and scalability, utilizing a proof-of-history consensus mechanism. It supports decentralized applications and cryptocurrencies, and is involved in the migration of AI16Z tokens.

entities.name: ChatGPT
entities.description: An AI chatbot developed by OpenAI, based on the GPT architecture. It is designed to understand and generate human-like text in response to prompts and questions.

entities.name: Gemini
entities.description: A large language model developed by Google AI. It is designed to be multimodal and capable of understanding and processing various types of information, including text and code.

entities.name: Grok
entities.description: An AI developed by xAI, designed to answer questions with a bit of the 'sarcastic' and 'rebellious' tone. It aims to provide information with a distinct personality.

entities.name: elizaOS token
